The House Committee on Rules offers the following substitute to HR 72:
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on Cancer Care Access; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, rural Georgians and minority populations in this state often lack access to
3 quality cancer care and there is a need to evaluate and make recommendations for such care;
4 and
5 WHEREAS, ideas and incentives to increase cancer screenings statewide should be
6 evaluated, including a return on investment assessment of prevention and early detection
7 efforts, to determine quality cancer care; and
8 WHEREAS, the economic impact and significance of cancer care centers and other care
9 facilities in Georgia needs to be explored; and
10 WHEREAS, medical education programs that attract and retain cancer physicians, nurses,
11 advance practice providers, and clinical researchers are important to this state; and
12 WHEREAS, workforce development initiatives for cancer care providers including those
13 described herein as well as licensed clinical social workers, community health workers, and
14 navigators may benefit this state.
- 1 -

